text.section:
A person may fish for finfish in the Chesapeake Bay or its tidal tributaries or in State waters of the Atlantic Ocean and coastal bays and their tributaries without a Chesapeake Bay and coastal sport fishing license if the person:
Is under the age of 16;
Possesses a valid commercial license;
Holds a valid tidal water sport fishing license issued by the State of Virginia, Potomac River Fisheries Commission, or District of Columbia, provided that this exemption shall not take effect until the Secretary has published notice in the Maryland Register of the Secretary's determination that the Virginia, Potomac River Fisheries Commission, or District of Columbia requirements for a tidal water sport fishing license are substantially similar to and reciprocal with the Chesapeake Bay and coastal sport fishing license requirements of this section;
Is fishing pursuant to any special charter boat license issued under subsection (d)(1) of this section;
Is on active duty with the armed forces of the United States;
Is a resident of this State;
Is on leave from the armed forces; and
Has, while fishing, a copy of the person's official leave orders;
Fishes on a free fishing day designated by the Secretary;
Holds a current resident consolidated senior sport fishing license issued under § 4-216 of this title;
Holds a current registration issued under subsection (d)(3) of this section; or
Is fishing on a commercial fishing pier licensed under subsection (d)(4) of this section.
